1. Revise NOx and CO emission factors for marine VCUs;
2. Revise tank emissions based on as-built drawings;
3. Revise EPN names;
4. Update equipment leak fugitive components;
5. Increase tank and fugitive H2S to 50 ppmw, leaving H2S concentration for
marine loading at 10 ppmw;
6. Increase annual throughputs;
7. Update LHV to HHV in combustion emission calcs;
8. Authorize loading at Docks 3, 6, 8, and 9; and
9. Incorporate PBR 159913 and NRSP for PCP 162551.

The marine (barge and ship) loading is limited to a yearly throughput of 689,580,000 barrels.
